# Project Development Rules

These rules apply to every change made in this repository. Follow them without exception.

## 1. TypeScript Only

Write all code in TypeScript. Never create or modify `.js` or `.jsx` files.
Use proper types imported from `payload` and the generated `payload-types.ts`.

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'
import type { User } from '@/payload-types'

// ❌ Wrong - no plain JS, no implicit `any`
const config = { slug: 'posts' }
```

## 2. Do Not Delete Working Files

Never delete files that contain working code. Only remove files that are confirmed dead code or explicitly requested for removal in the task description.

## 3. Do Not Refactor Unrelated Files

Limit every change to files that are directly required by the current task.
Do not reformat, rename, reorganize, or restructure any code that is outside the scope of the change.

## 4. Plan Before Editing

Before writing any code, produce a short written plan that lists:
- Which files will be created or modified
- What will change in each file and why

Do not start coding until the plan is clear.

## 5. Keep Payload Collections Modular

Each collection must live in its own file inside `src/collections/`.
Export exactly one `CollectionConfig` constant per file.
Register all collections in `payload.config.ts`.

```
src/collections/
├── Users.ts
├── Media.ts
└── Products.ts   ← one file per collection
```

## 6. Create Reusable Access Helpers

All access control functions belong in `src/access/`.
Extract every repeated access pattern into a named helper and import it where needed.
Never inline the same access logic in more than one place.

```typescript
// src/access/adminOnly.ts
import type { Access } from 'payload'

export const adminOnly: Access = ({ req: { user } }) =>
  Boolean(user?.roles?.includes('admin'))
```

## 7. Preserve Cloudflare Compatibility

This project runs on **Cloudflare Workers** with **D1 (SQLite)** and **R2**.

- ❌ Do NOT use Node.js-only APIs: `fs`, `path`, `crypto` (node:crypto), `Buffer`, `stream`, `child_process`, etc.
- ❌ Do NOT use `pino-pretty` in production (use the console logger configured in `payload.config.ts`).
- ❌ Do NOT add npm packages that depend on native Node modules.
- ✅ Use the Web Platform APIs available in Workers (fetch, crypto via `globalThis.crypto`, etc.).
- ✅ Test locally with `pnpm dev` (Wrangler) before marking work complete.

## 8. Explain Every Changed File

For every file you create or modify, provide a brief explanation of:
- What changed
- Why it was necessary

Include this in the PR description, commit message, or as an inline comment when the reason is non-obvious.

## 9. Run Build/Typecheck After Edits

After every set of changes, run all of the following that apply:

```bash
# Type-check TypeScript
pnpm typecheck          # or: npx tsc --noEmit

# Build for Cloudflare Workers
pnpm build

# Generate updated Payload types (after schema changes)
pnpm payload generate:types

# Regenerate admin import map (after adding/removing components)
pnpm payload generate:importmap
```

Do not submit changes that fail the typecheck or build.
